->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull has-background-dim-70 has-foreground-dark-background-color has-background-dim\" style=\"background-image:url(https://marinellayule.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/20180917_191754.jpg)\"><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":96} -->\n<div style=\"height:96px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"has-text-align-center margin-bottom-half\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center margin-bottom-half\">News</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"margin-top-half\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"has-text-align-center margin-top-half\">Recent Marketing Articles</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:latest-posts {\"align\":\"wide\",\"postsToShow\":3,\"displayPostContent\":true,\"displayPostDate\":true,\"postLayout\":\"grid\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":96} -->\n<div style=\"height:96px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->\n\n<!-- wp:cover {\"url\":\"https://marinellayule.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/20191016_190825.jpg\",\"id\":20,\"dimRatio\":70,\"overlayColor\":\"foreground-dark\",\"focalPoint\":{\"x\":\"0.52\",\"y\":\"0.44\"},\"align\":\"full\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull has-background-dim-70 has-foreground-dark-background-color has-background-dim\" style=\"background-image:url(https://marinellayule.files.wordpress.com/2019/10/20191016_190825.jpg);background-position:52% 44%\"><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":96} -->\n<div style=\"height:96px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"has-text-align-center\">About Marinella</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have lived in a variety of places around the world, including: United States, my home country, Argentina, and Czechia. Now I consider myself a Montreal-er after living a full year there - and yes, I survived the winter!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I studied marketing and film at a university in Boston and proceed to move to Prague, Czechia to work at a start up as their SEO and blogging marketer. From there, I traveled around and then found a home in Montreal, Canada where I was able to work with a marketing agency doing campaigns and then onto another start up as their marketing director.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tired of pursuing dreams of people who saw me as just a number, I decided to branch out on my own to help build businesses of fellow entrepreneurs and independent thinkers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My love for languages have blossomed through my travels and it has given me the opportunity to work in Spanish as well as in English. Puedo hablar y escribir en español sin problema. J’apprend le français mais je peux faire différentes choses. Along with learning languages, I am certified to teach English and have taught English writing and speaking skills.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I would be honored to bring to your business this international eye for design, copy, and marketing strategy and implementation!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:button {\"textColor\":\"background\",\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"is-style-outline\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button aligncenter is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-background-color has-text-color\">Contact</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":96} -->\n<div style=\"height:96px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->','','','publish','closed','closed','','home-2','','','2020-09-30 02:50:46','2020-09-30 02:50:46','',0,'http://local.marinellayule.com/?page_id=422',0,'page','',0),(423,1,'2020-05-30 19:41:04','2020-05-30 19:41:04','','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2020-05-30 19:41:04','2020-05-30 19:41:04','',0,'http://local.marinellayule.com/home/',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(454,1,'2020-04-10 11:24:58','2020-04-10 15:24:58','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This isn\'t going to be an article about what is good customer service in the sense of refunds, trouble shootings, etc. This is more in line on MARKETING and SELLING. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to explain, let me share a story. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>When Things Change, Change With Them</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Due to the Coronavirus, many fitness professionals had to move their training and jobs online. Some were already personal trainers and perhaps had some online components while others were fitness instructors at gyms and studios that worked on a schedule and were paid by the owner rather than the actual fitness customers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I attended a fitness studio and one of my regular fitness instructors was one who now had to work somehow virtually. I posted on my Instagram story that I was stretching from home because of the quarantine order and she reached out to me saying she had online fitness classes and that we should get together. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From a personal stand point, I didn\'t need these online fitness classes because I am pretty fitness self-motivated, but she is one of my favorite instructors so I kept her in mind for <strong>REFERRALS </strong>that I could send her way. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It so happens that the next day, a friend of mine was telling me how she misses fitness classes (she went to a different studio) and that she isn\'t motivated enough to do it on her own. I remembered my instructor and said I would ask her what her prices were and what she offered, which my friend appreciated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I contacted my instructor and after a few messages back and forth for clarifying questions, she never got back to me. And later, I saw her advertising on her Instagram for virtual classes, just DM her. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Where Future Customers Come From</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I haven\'t reached back out to my instructor for two reasons:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>My friend wasn\'t too concerned about the classes.</li><li>I believe it is the instructor\'s job (or the entrepreneur) to follow up with potential customer questions. </li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I was offering her a potential customer and who knows, future customers, but because she brushed me off, I won\'t refer anymore. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You don\'t know who can and will refer you. The best is to practice best customer service to everyone even if it isn\'t the people who will eventually be a customer. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Customer Service Tips</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are my thoughts on what she should have done from a marketing perspective:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Responded in a <strong>TIMELY MANNER</strong>.</li><li>Created a <strong>RATE SHEET</strong> (which I asked her if she had one) and given it to me.<ul><li>A <strong>RATE SHEET</strong> is a document that details what you offer and for how much. </li></ul></li><li>Or just typed out in the private message what the rates would be. </li><li>Or, just told me she didn\'t have the information at that time and would get back to me soon (and then get back to me).</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Another Story on Customer Service</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I had another friend, before the Coronavirus, that was looking for a personal trainer. I used to work with someone in marketing who became a fitness coach and I messaged her as well on Instagram. This is what happened:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>She responded to me quickly and with lots of information.</li><li>She asked about my friend to make sure <em>she could help her properly</em>.</li><li>When my friend told me to exchange their numbers, my old co-worker was prompt in answering her questions.</li><li>My friend became one of her clients and is now a happy customer.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have since recommended my old co-worker to many others looking for a personal trainer. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The biggest takeaway from this should be responding in a timely manner with as much information as possible even if that information is, \"May I please get back to you?\" No one likes being <em>left on read</em> especially when everyone in today\'s society is on their phone. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As an entrepreneur or a small business owner, you never know where the next client will come from. You never know who will be championing your name. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":461,\"width\":396,\"height\":395,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://marinellayule.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/12.png?w=1024\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-461\" width=\"396\" height=\"395\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>The Art of Business Growth</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In my professional opinion, what happened with my fitness instructor was that she did not do much thinking before promoting her virtual classes. What I mean, she didn\'t think through the different marketing and selling steps and, most likely, only thought about using a video call program and that people would send her money digitally such as Paypal, Interac, Venmo, etc. She would be at home doing what she does best through her laptop. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unfortunately, business requires more planning and though marketing isn\'t the most necessary business function (in comparison to accountants and taxes), when it comes to the art of customer service, every marketing and selling step needs to be thought out thoroughly or you risk losing a potential customer or referral source. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One last story, Facebook groups are marvelous for people looking to market and sell their services. You can frame the conversations and show your value by offering advice and some of your service for free. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A business friend of mine created a group and in it she gives business tips for improving your business and reaching your full potential. She has offered many live video training sessions and created free 3 Day Business Coaching Sessions. Through this, I got to see how valuable her services are and since then have been referring her left and right. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Each business is different, but for my fitness instructor, here are some marketing tips I suggest. You may also use this in your own business if you feel it applies to you and your schedule.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Business Growth Advice</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Analyze <strong>WHO </strong>your target audience is. Example: If you are a fitness trainer for new moms, join mom groups.</li><li>Create either a <strong>PDF RATE SHEET</strong> or <strong>Website/Landing Page</strong> that holds information about you and what you are offering. There are many free programs and sites for this!</li><li><strong>Create a Facebook group</strong> where you can offer insights and engage with customers and potential customers alike.</li><li>Do <strong>Lives </strong>on Instagram and Facebook for the customers and potential customers with more insights. </li><li><strong>Join other Facebook Groups</strong> to spread the word about you and your services. Make sure to join groups that have your target audience. </li><li><strong>Offer Free Consultations or Exchange Services</strong> for a testimonial or for a service your customer offers (example: fitness classes in exchange for marketing materials). </li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Customer service doesn\'t mean after a client purchases from you or when the client is upset. Customer service starts way before you have a client. That is the real art of customer service. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If any of these resonate with you and you would like to chat about your target audience, how to market your business, or how to create marketing materials, don\'t hesitate to reach out! Contact me via <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">email </a>or <a href=\"http://www.instagram.com/myopenpassport/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Instagram</a>!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','The Art of Customer Service','Customer Service happens immediately when you start selling and marketing your business. ','publish','open','open','','the-art-of-customer-service','','','2020-05-31 23:36:23','2020-05-31 23:36:23','',0,'http://local.marinellayule.com/?p=454',0,'post','',1),(473,1,'2020-06-12 18:39:45','2020-06-12 18:39:45','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a marketing and branding professional, I have been seeing a lot of people, future entrepreneurs, turning to the virtual world to start businesses especially during this lock down time. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since people\'s budgets are limited when starting a new business, I thought to create a marketing guide to help get the ball rolling. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Things Future Entrepreneurs Should Know</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Know Your Target Audience</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Entrepreneurs are so passionate about their product or service they seem to forget if it is what their target market is looking for? If this is a service or product people are interested in, is your branding resonating to them? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Future entrepreneurs should pick a logo and colors that resonate with the target market. Your target market will be more eager to engage if they relate to your company more than just the need for your product or service. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Prepare a Business/Marketing Plan</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that you know your target market, a wise course of action is to list out the different steps you can take in your business and marketing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A lot of entrepreneurs are not sure how to start their business or online presence. They have too much they want to do. The best for future entrepreneurs is to list everything out and order them via priority and what is easy to cross off your list.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Studies show that crossing items off your list makes you more confident for the rest of tasks. Do the easy ones and the most necessary ones first. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Go Outside Your Comfort Zone</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Entrepreneurs know that starting your own business is scary. It definitely can be considered going outside your comfort zone. For future entrepreneurs, the biggest advice is to just do it! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You will feel uncomfortable and you will feel nervous, but the end result will be worth it!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Network</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is a lot to be said about marketing and SEO. Future entrepreneurs should set up their online presence to make sure they are being promoted efficiently and effectively. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, a big part of <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/social-media-platforms/\">social media</a> and regular business is Word of Mouth. A big part of this is networking. This also applies to going outside your comfort zone. If you are not a people person, you will have to become on.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Virtual coffees are now a popular thing. The more you talk about your business, the more others will learn and spread the word about you. There isn\'t much a <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/in-person-and-online-networking/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">difference between in person and virtual networking</a> in today\'s society. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Word of Mouth</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You never know where your next client will come from. Do not <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/the-art-of-customer-service/\">pass up any opportunity</a> to network or follow leads. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Something might seem small to you, but it could lead to something even bigger.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The ability to follow leads, big or small, goes back to knowing your target market and planning out your business and marketing plan, having a clear view of where you want to go.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are looking for branding, marketing, or business help, please get in touch. Let\'s bring your brand vision to life!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\"><!-- wp:button {\"className\":\"is-style-outline\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\" href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">Contact</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->','Things Future Entrepreneurs Should Know','Learn about these top 5 things future entrepreneurs should know about starting their business in today\'s society.','publish','open','open','','things-future-entrepreneurs-should-know','','','2020-06-12 18:41:00','2020-06-12 18:41:00','',0,'http://local.marinellayule.com/?p=473',0,'post','',0),(479,1,'2020-04-15 12:20:00','2020-04-15 16:20:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are so many social media platforms out there and it can be overwhelming for new or established entrepreneurs. Often people make the mistake of either jumping into all of them or not using any.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unfortunately, in today\'s society, some social media presence is necessary. However, it doesn\'t mean you have to be on all of them!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The biggest determining factor is WHO is your target market? This will lead you to decide WHERE they are. Also, WHAT is your business. This again will also determine which social media platforms are the best to promote your goods and services. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":492,\"width\":470,\"height\":470,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://marinellayule.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/14.png?w=1024\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-492\" width=\"470\" height=\"470\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Snapchat</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Snapchat was originally created for sexual pictures. The fact that pictures and videos disappear right after you view them helps significantly for this. However, many also use this to share funny pictures of themselves or foods they are eating. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Snapchat is still very much present in social media, but the user base has changed. It used to be Millennials, but as they grew and got older, they have shifted their attention away. Now, Gen Z (born after 1996) are quite dominant on this platform. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From a business perspective, Snapchat is a good platform if you are targeting younger adults or teenagers. However, the marketing content needs to be more challenges and content that will only last a few seconds. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The businesses that prosper with Snapchat are more magazine type companies that have their own section in the \"Discover\" part of the app. Here, they can post stories about different pop cultural events and celebrities. Some bigger international brands also have a section such as fashion companies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In regards to which social media platforms you should use, for the average small business owner, however, I do not suggest putting effort into the app for your business. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Pinterest</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The demographics of Pinterest is mainly women. If your target market is women, and specifically moms, this is the platform you should be on. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.goldenbloggerz.com/pinterest-strategy-for-bloggers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">concept of Pinterest</a> is pretty simple: think scrap book. There are \"pins\" or photos with information on them that allows the viewer to click on it and be taken to the site that created that pin. For example, if the pin has information about the best baby clothes, the viewer can click on the image itself and be transferred to the baby clothes company. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pinterest recently changed its algorithm so that new pins are worth more. So the more new pins you can create and post the better. There are a variety of scheduling tools that can help you determine when your pins will be seen and keep track of analytics. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In regards to which social media platforms you should devote time into, this platform is great for any type of blogger or businesses that have a blog and cater to women. If this is your niche and target market, go for it!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Facebook</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Facebook used to be the King of all social media, but now I would say it is more a parliamentary or congressional system. Even though Facebook does own Instagram and Whatsapp, it not longer reigns over everyone\'s lives as it used to.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This being said, there are many people still on Facebook, but the main demographic are more older- Gen Y and Baby Boomers. They still use it for what is originally was created for being connecting with family and friends. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Groups and Marketplace</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the rest of the ages and including Gen Y and Baby Boomers, Facebook has turned more into a casual Linkedin meaning that it is being used for more business purposes. People go to Facebook to check restaurant information and reviews or they join groups to network for business or support groups. No matter what you are looking for, there is a group on Facebook for it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On top of this, Facebook also has Marketplace, which allows people to sell items in their area such as used desks or clothes. In some countries, Facebook has even rolled out a dating function, but with major competitors like Tinder and Bumble, I personally and professionally doubt it will be a success. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In regards to business, having a Facebook page is good when displaying information and gathering reviews from the average consumer. However, pages are no longer the place to get engagement from your target base. Just like Instagram, engagement is now what people aim for and what these social media algorithms love. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to groups and pages, one big thing you can do on Facebook is do Live videos of yourself or your company. I recommend doing lives in groups, but you can do pages as well! It gets you connected with your community and they can see and connect with you in return!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are an expert in your field, my recommendation is to start a Facebook group funneling in people that could be your potential client. By giving value to the group and engaging with your members, they will be more likely to purchase your product or service one day or at least <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/2020/04/10/the-art-of-customer-service/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">refer you to someone who will</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you sell a product, having a Facebook page helps with your Instagram account. You can connect the two allowing you to create a \"Shop\" button on your Instagram pictures. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your target market is the main demographic that uses Facebook, then Facebook ads might be worth the price; however, there is nothing better than engage with customers and creating a word of mouth network. Which social media platforms? How about Facebook?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Instagram</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instagram has changed its algorithm a lot recently. It has hidden likes and many believe that it will also hide followers soon. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From a psychological perspective, seeing the amount of likes and followers increases your chances to gaining more. The more people see you have likes and followers the more likely they will think you are popular and worth liking and following. The majority of us don\'t want to be left out, which is why once Tik Tok started rolling, many people jumped on board relatively quick- to not feel left out. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, due to people buying likes and the bullying behind it, likes have now been hidden. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even still, Instagram is a great platform to showcase photos of you, your product, your services, and or your brand! What you post needs to be in line with your brand. If you are a life coach, posting photos of your thoughts, you, quotes that inspire, testimonials, etc are part of you who are and your message- your brand. If you are a fashion company, posting photos of your outfits and accessories is part of what you do. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Engage, Engage, Engage</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The biggest advice for Instagram is engage with other accounts, specifically accounts that are in your target audience. If you are a fashion company, engage with lifestyle accounts, fashion bloggers, etc. Comment actually comments rather than emojis are \"Great picture\" to make an engagement worth it. Otherwise there is no point.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The next big advice, know your hashtags. Instagram penalizes you for using the same hashtags over and over (unless it is a new one you created that is specific to you- many do this for a wedding). Try to switch up your hashtags every few photos and do ones that your target audience would be searching. In addition to hashtags, be sure to include your location as some people search via that.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, tag major accounts in the photo. This will be put in their \"tagged\" section of their Instagram profile so other people will then see it. That major account might also acknowledge it and give you a shout out too!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All of this to eventually say, the main demographic of Instagram are Millennials with some flow over to Gen Y and Z. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This demographic also has a short attention span so the use of stories is key. These stories are short timed photos or videos that can be interactive. Did I mention engagement is key? Sometimes, viewers only look at stories rather than your postings. And, your account can be found via your stories as well. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can now save your stories into your highlights so future account visitors can see all they have missed. This is great if you want to save any useful industry tips or special occasion broadcasts. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In line with this and like Facebook, Instagram offers live videos as well via the stories. You can also pair up with another account and do a dual live video which can increase your viewership and therefore prospective clients and followers! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In one sentence for the question \"which social media platforms\" : <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/2020/01/31/what-i-have-learned-from-instagram/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Instagram </a>is now all about connections in a personal way between brands and consumers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Tik Tok</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The infamous and new kid on the block, Tik Tok! Everyone is talking about it, many are joining it, and the majority seem confused about it in general. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unlike Snapchat, there is actually a business benefit to this platform. The biggest for entrepreneurs are businesses that specialize in fashion and beauty, food, or fitness. There might be a few others, but unlike Instagram, Tik Tok is ONLY videos. So, your brand has to be video appropraite.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meaning, can you translate your product or service into a video? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On top of this, the demographic is mainly Gen Z. This means the average age on the platform are 16 year old\'s. Is your target audience this younger crowd? If so, then you need to be on this platform!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In regards to the actual video content, these videos are in lined with lip syncing and dancing. There are a variety of trends that I recommend businesses follow. Such as \"Flip the Switch\" where two people switch clothes and positions in the middle of the video by \"flipping the switch\" or turning the light on and off to hide the transformation. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is perfect for fashion or beauty companies because they can show changes in outfits and make ups quickly. Oh, yeah, videos are less than a minute long. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are some comedy skits there, but again, it has to go along with your brand. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>YouTube</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I don\'t really consider YouTube a social media platform and more like a search engine. Unlike the other platforms you don\'t need an account to watch endless hours of videos. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most people nowadays look up tutorials and instructions on YouTube rather than reading a manual or blog. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, there are many content creators that bring you all sorts of news, travel tips, language advice, fashion, etc. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The videos can be longer than the one minute on Tik Tok, but be warned, any video longer than 10 minutes will see a drop off rate in views. People don\'t have the attention like they used to. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With any platform, liking, subscribing, and commenting helps your account within the algorithm. But, YouTube is unique in that the more views you have the more money you can make from ads. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While there are Influencers on Instagram, they get paid per post or a commission when they are an ambassador of a brand or product. YouTubers get money per view and or visitor who has watched that video. Major YouTubers can make 100Ks every month based on ads. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In regards to smaller businesses, I suggest not spending marketing efforts in this direction unless your brand and product/service is made for videos, but even still, creating and editing a well done video for YouTube can be a lot of resources.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Twitter</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I also don\'t really view Twitter as a social media platform in the sense of Facebook, Instagram, and Tik Tok. Users do need an account and there are followers, likes, retweets, etc, but it is more for dispersing information such as news or Press Releases rather than sharing branding. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many bloggers use it as a form of sharing new blog posts, but most users use Twitter to follow major people such as celebrities or politicians, news media, and major companies that might be offering promotions. As well as to complain to companies. Companies tend to have faster customer service when the complaint is in public and not in email.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Linkedin</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Linkedin is a weird social media platform. There are a variety of business platforms available, but Linkedin has remained King in this category.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a good rule of thumb, as a business professional, it is good to have a profile. If you are new to the business world and are starting your own company, I suggest creating a profile anyways at least in your business\' name. This will help you connect with other business professionals that could be your client or help your business grow. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are a service that helps other businesses or entrepreneurs, I highly recommend having a Linkedin profile. If this is also your target market, posting consistently and <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/2020/01/15/in-person-and-online-networking/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">reaching out to people</a> is of the same importance as Instagram and Facebook. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The key with any and all of this, is to know where your target market is and be more active on that platform. In regards to demographics, Linkedin has a wide range of ages and generations, but the big market is business professionals and those helping business professionals. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I hope this helps in creating your online presence for your business! Feel free to reach out for any more marketing strategy tips!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\" href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">Contact</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Which Social Media Platforms are Good for You?','Confused with all the different social media platforms? Here is a break down of each and the reason you might use or not use them!','publish','open','open','','social-media-platforms','','','2020-06-29 19:48:38','2020-06-29 19:48:38','',0,'http://local.marinellayule.com/?p=479',0,'post','',0),(555,1,'2020-05-11 11:35:02','2020-05-11 15:35:02','<!-- wp:image {\"id\":545,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-rounded\"><a href=\"https://myopenpassport.net/\"><img src=\"https://marinellayule.files.wordpress.com/2020/05/7.png?w=450\" alt=\"My Open Passport Travel Blog \" class=\"wp-image-545\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":542,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-rounded\"><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/articles/\"><img src=\"https://marinellayule.files.wordpress.com/2020/05/4.png?w=450\" alt=\"Lear more about marketing\" class=\"wp-image-542\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":724,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-rounded\"><a href=\"https://myopenpassport.net/category/travel-insights-and-tips-etc/interview-series/\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/linktree-for-instagram.png\" alt=\"Interview series: expats and intercultural love\" class=\"wp-image-724\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":539,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-rounded\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCq3EFtJva8fSeFLQJQOborQ/videos\"><img src=\"https://marinellayule.files.wordpress.com/2020/05/1.png?w=450\" alt=\"Visit My YouTube\" class=\"wp-image-539\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":725,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-rounded\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TBDfMQ27Asw\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/linktree-for-instagram-1.png\" alt=\"YouTube Video concerning BLM\" class=\"wp-image-725\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Instagram Links','','publish','closed','closed','','instagram-links','','','2020-10-05 11:41:27','2020-10-05 11:41:27','',0,'http://local.marinellayule.com/?page_id=555',0,'page','',0),(585,1,'2020-09-23 19:54:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Build a Business, now!</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now is the time to start building your own business. Why now? Because there is no better time. There will also be something that comes up so, <strong><em>why not start now</em></strong>? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You might be asking yourself, how do I start? I don\'t know where to begin. I don\'t have the money to invest into setting up my website and the marketing. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What if I told you, you can do it all by <strong><em>yourself</em></strong>? You don\'t need to spend thousands of dollars for a service.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the saying goes, give a man a fish, he eats for a day, teach the man how to fish, he eats for life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Well, grab your fishing pole because that\'s what we are talking about here!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"has-text-align-center\">Coming soon: Build a Business eCourse</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An eCourse to help entrepreneurs just like you build their business! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Here is what the course covers:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Branding and Target Market Visualization</li><li>How to do your own branding and logo design</li><li>Information on different websites and website hosting</li><li>How to build your own website</li><li>Basic coding information for website tweaks</li><li>Free tools you can use for marketing projects</li><li>Competitor Research</li><li>SEO: All you need to know</li><li>Plugins for your website to make it run even better</li><li>Further marketing ideas and content creations</li><li>Bookkeeping tips and tricks</li><li>Networking and building relationships for your business </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is your one stop shop for all your building needs. I give you the Legos and the rest is up to you! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>HOWEVER!</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Just because you are doing it by yours