 /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once this step is complete, then it would be actually creating the content!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1018,\"width\":497,\"height\":497,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/20-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Creating a social media strategy by Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant\" class=\"wp-image-1018\" width=\"497\" height=\"497\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I hope this article helped you in understanding the social media strategy process and some thought processes a marketer goes through in preparation for a complimentary call or before they market your business. Feel free to schedule your <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery call</a> with me to jump start your marketing or social media strategy! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong>Build a Business eCourse</strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from target markets to building a website to SEO to marketing. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Steps in Creating a Social Media Strategy','','inherit','closed','closed','','1015-revision-v1','','','2020-09-23 18:31:15','2020-09-23 18:31:15','',1015,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1015-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1021,1,'2020-09-23 18:35:51','2020-09-23 18:35:51','','23','','inherit','open','closed','','23','','','2020-10-01 14:12:54','2020-10-01 14:12:54','',1013,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/23.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1022,1,'2020-09-23 18:36:34','2020-09-23 18:36:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Complimentary discovery calls are not as popular as one would think. Many business professionals don’t offer it and others have a strict rule on when they do jump on a call. Others still feel uncomfortable with being on a phone call let alone a video call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What? We have to put on a nice shirt? Yes, yes you do.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I offer <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery calls</a> to potential clients as a way to “meet and greet.” I use this time to get to know the potential client, but also for them to get to know me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some reasons why you should take the chance to get on a complimentary discovery call if you are the potential client and reasons if you are the business professional:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Complimentary Discovery Calls for the Potential Client</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can see the person</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Emails and messages are great, but, who is on the other side? In this age of online profiles and cat fishing, are we sure that that person’s photo is actually the person? You will be entrusting your business into the hands of this person, it is a good idea to see them “in person” or at least a video call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can ask on the spot questions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you have a video call or you meet in person, there isn’t an opportunity for the person to look up answers. As a potential client, you should want to see if the person really knows their stuff and if they don’t, how do they answer the question?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You get a feel of their personality</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Did you know, most of a message is sent via body language and tone of voice? Only like 5 percent of a message is the actual words. Talking to the person in person or via video will enable you to see how they really are. Do they have more of a vibrant personality? Do they appear more quiet and serious? There is no wrong personality, but as a potential client, you will want to work with someone who resonates with you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Reasons for the Business Professional</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can ask more in depth questions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many things to know that will help you price out a quote or to let you know if the contract fits into your niche. Sending emails and messages could cover all these questions, but often it could take many emails back and forth. Having an in person meeting or a video call will enable you to ask all the questions you need within 30 minutes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can get a sense of the scope of work</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes clients don’t know 100 percent what they are looking for. Sometimes clients say “I know it when I see it.” You might have certain phrases that are a <em>\"no go</em>\" when working with clients. Certain phrases might mean certain things about the client such as a specific project might take longer with one client than another due to the client’s personality or expectations of the work flow.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can put your best foot forward</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just as I mentioned above, most of the message is through body language and tone of voice. Before your video call or in person meeting, dress your best, brush your teeth, and make sure you are smiling! I know many women don’t like the word “Smile!” But, it really does change the conversation when you do. It conveys a happy and bright personality. Try it in the mirror. Say this with a straight face and then a smile: “My name is ___ and I love what I do.” Which sounded better?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, You can show you have studied their situation through reading your notes. People love when others do research – it shows them you care about them and their business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>For Complimentary Discovery Calls</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For myself, I use Calendly to schedule my complimentary discovery calls. It automatically sets the time for them in their time zone and then once it is scheduled, it appears in my calendar with the time in my time zone. I could also set it up to automatically send a Zoom or Google Meet link.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Make sure to follow up with them a few hours before with the link again to make sure there are no technical difficulties.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I pitch my services, I always include a sentence that discusses jumping on a call and if the person is agreeable to it, I send them the link to my Calendly. This takes away the back and forth of when both of you are available and any issues with time zone confusions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1021,\"width\":553,\"height\":553,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/23-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Complimentary Discovery Calls and why you need them with Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant\" class=\"wp-image-1021\" width=\"553\" height=\"553\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Don’t Ghost Complimentary Discovery Calls</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both the business professional and the potential client, the best and absolute must thing you have to do when it comes to complimentary discovery calls is to show up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>OR, send an email with a postponement or cancellation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It isn’t professional on either side to not show up for a scheduled call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But from another point of view, as the potential client, it is free! Why not use this time to your benefit?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The reasons for a business professional might be obvious: you will lose the potential client. But there are drawbacks for the client as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even if you decide to not hire the business professional you never know where connections will lead you. Think of complimentary discovery calls as another form of networking. Just because you can’t afford their services doesn’t mean that they might not be able to help you in other ways.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They might recommend people to you as clients for you! Or they might know of another professional that could help in your budget range.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both professional and potential client, the best rule of thumb is to be polite and positive when interacting with each other.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Complimentary Discovery Calls and Why You Need to Do Them','','inherit','closed','closed','','1013-revision-v1','','','2020-09-23 18:36:34','2020-09-23 18:36:34','',1013,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1013-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1023,1,'2020-09-23 18:38:45','2020-09-23 18:38:45','','22','','inherit','open','closed','','22','','','2020-09-23 18:39:04','2020-09-23 18:39:04','',1013,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/22.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1024,1,'2020-09-23 18:39:54','2020-09-23 18:39:54','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Complimentary discovery calls are not as popular as one would think. Many business professionals don’t offer it and others have a strict rule on when they do jump on a call. Others still feel uncomfortable with being on a phone call let alone a video call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What? We have to put on a nice shirt? Yes, yes you do.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I offer <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery calls</a> to potential clients as a way to “meet and greet.” I use this time to get to know the potential client, but also for them to get to know me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some reasons why you should take the chance to get on a complimentary discovery call if you are the potential client and reasons if you are the business professional:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Complimentary Discovery Calls for the Potential Client</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can see the person</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Emails and messages are great, but, who is on the other side? In this age of online profiles and cat fishing, are we sure that that person’s photo is actually the person? You will be entrusting your business into the hands of this person, it is a good idea to see them “in person” or at least a video call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can ask on the spot questions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you have a video call or you meet in person, there isn’t an opportunity for the person to look up answers. As a potential client, you should want to see if the person really knows their stuff and if they don’t, how do they answer the question?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You get a feel of their personality</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Did you know, most of a message is sent via body language and tone of voice? Only like 5 percent of a message is the actual words. Talking to the person in person or via video will enable you to see how they really are. Do they have more of a vibrant personality? Do they appear more quiet and serious? There is no wrong personality, but as a potential client, you will want to work with someone who resonates with you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Reasons for the Business Professional</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can ask more in depth questions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many things to know that will help you price out a quote or to let you know if the contract fits into your niche. Sending emails and messages could cover all these questions, but often it could take many emails back and forth. Having an in person meeting or a video call will enable you to ask all the questions you need within 30 minutes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can get a sense of the scope of work</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes clients don’t know 100 percent what they are looking for. Sometimes clients say “I know it when I see it.” You might have certain phrases that are a <em>\"no go</em>\" when working with clients. Certain phrases might mean certain things about the client such as a specific project might take longer with one client than another due to the client’s personality or expectations of the work flow.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can put your best foot forward</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just as I mentioned above, most of the message is through body language and tone of voice. Before your video call or in person meeting, dress your best, brush your teeth, and make sure you are smiling! I know many women don’t like the word “Smile!” But, it really does change the conversation when you do. It conveys a happy and bright personality. Try it in the mirror. Say this with a straight face and then a smile: “My name is ___ and I love what I do.” Which sounded better?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, You can show you have studied their situation through reading your notes. People love when others do research – it shows them you care about them and their business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>For Complimentary Discovery Calls</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For myself, I use Calendly to schedule my complimentary discovery calls. It automatically sets the time for them in their time zone and then once it is scheduled, it appears in my calendar with the time in my time zone. I could also set it up to automatically send a Zoom or Google Meet link.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Make sure to follow up with them a few hours before with the link again to make sure there are no technical difficulties.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I pitch my services, I always include a sentence that discusses jumping on a call and if the person is agreeable to it, I send them the link to my Calendly. This takes away the back and forth of when both of you are available and any issues with time zone confusions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1021,\"width\":553,\"height\":553,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/23-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Complimentary Discovery Calls and why you need them with Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant\" class=\"wp-image-1021\" width=\"553\" height=\"553\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Don’t Ghost Complimentary Discovery Calls</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both the business professional and the potential client, the best and absolute must thing you have to do when it comes to complimentary discovery calls is to show up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>OR, send an email with a postponement or cancellation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It isn’t professional on either side to not show up for a scheduled call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But from another point of view, as the potential client, it is free! Why not use this time to your benefit?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The reasons for a business professional might be obvious: you will lose the potential client. But there are drawbacks for the client as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even if you decide to not hire the business professional you never know where connections will lead you. Think of complimentary discovery calls as another form of networking. Just because you can’t afford their services doesn’t mean that they might not be able to help you in other ways.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They might recommend people to you as clients for you! Or they might know of another professional that could help in your budget range.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both professional and potential client, the best rule of thumb is to be polite and positive when interacting with each other.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong>Build a Business eCourse</strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from branding to networking to invoicing to hiring someone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Complimentary Discovery Calls and Why You Need to Do Them','','inherit','closed','closed','','1013-revision-v1','','','2020-09-23 18:39:54','2020-09-23 18:39:54','',1013,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1013-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1025,1,'2020-09-23 18:41:45','2020-09-23 18:41:45','','25','','inherit','open','closed','','25','','','2020-10-01 14:07:55','2020-10-01 14:07:55','',1011,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/25.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1026,1,'2020-09-23 18:42:36','2020-09-23 18:42:36','','24','','inherit','open','closed','','24','','','2020-09-23 18:43:04','2020-09-23 18:43:04','',1011,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/24.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1027,1,'2020-09-23 18:47:44','2020-09-23 18:47:44','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What is the difference between a marketing agency and a virtual assistant? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People nowadays are looking for a Virtual Assistant more and more. What is a Virtual Assistant? A Virtual Assistant is someone that is similar to a secretary or personal assistant, but online and virtually! They help in a wide range of tasks from organizing emails to customer service to some marketing tasks. The upside to Virtual Assistants is that they are usually cheaper than a marketing professional, consultant, or agency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Due to more and more business owners looking for marketing help and for a cheaper cost, entrepreneurs are turning to Virtual Assistants.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some reasons how marketing agencies and virtual assistants differ and what you need to think about before hiring one or the other.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1025,\"width\":690,\"height\":690,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/25-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"The difference between a marketing agency and a virtual assistant by Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant.\" class=\"wp-image-1025\" width=\"690\" height=\"690\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>A Marketing Agency is More Marketing Focused</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marketing Agencies are more marketing focused. Many entrepreneurs are looking for assistance in just marketing tasks. Marketing agents probably don’t offer email organizations or customer service when responding to your potential clients. However, with the marketing tasks, they know what they are doing and won’t need direct supervision or game plan. They are able to create one that best suits your business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Virtual Assistants are very smart and know their stuff. But, their stuff tends to be more email organizations, customer service, and social media media posting when they are told what and when to post. Not all of course, but many. If you have a lot of more clerical tasks, then a Virtual Assistant is the way to go. If you have more marketing tasks, consider a marketing agency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>You are Paying for the Thought Process</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One point that needs to bring up is the cost of a marketing agency versus Virtual Assistants. Virtual Assistants tend to be more budget friendly. However, marketing agencies come with a lot of marketing experience and background which justifies the higher costs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>It comes down to this question:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Would you like to hire someone who can contribute great ideas that are backed by data or someone who needs direction and is more of a support team member rather than a partner?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When looking into hiring a team member, partner, supporter, etc, look into that person’s experience and education in order to see what will be a good fit for what you are looking for.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>You Get More Ideas for Your Money</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Further into the costs, marketing agencies are always thinking of new ways to market your business efficiently and effectively. This is their bread and butter and most, if not all, marketing agencies, dream of new marketing strategies and new marketing content.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We can’t help it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even if you might be paying per hour for your marketing consultant, I guarantee you, at least for my own marketing agency, your marketing consultant is working more than what they are charging you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Further, due to a higher costs, marketing agencies probably don’t have many tasks daily day for their clients. Efficient and effective marketing agencies will have their content scheduled and prepared in order to have enough time between due dates to accommodate all clients. At least, that’s how it is for my marketing agency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Virtual Assistants tend to be hired for more daily tasks. With a more budget friendly pricing they might need to take on more clients to fill their own financial needs. This could lead them to being busy every day as they go from client to client.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>From Strategy to Content Creation to Implementation in a Marketing Agency and a Virtual Assistant</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marketing agencies are an agency. They know how the different pieces come into place. They create the strategy, create the content, and then schedule and post the content at the best times for your business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A Virtual Assistant can do this as well, but often they are required by a client or offer to their clients only content creation and or implementation. Not many Virtual Assistants can do all three.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Often, hiring multiple people can be more of a hassle than what it’s worth. It is possible to hire a marketing consultant for preparing a strategy and then giving it to someone else for content creation and then your Virtual Assistant for the implementation, but your VA might not fully understand or there might be miscommunication among the different pieces.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The more hands that are on a project, the higher the likelihood that there will be a problem. Diversity is good, but when files are being moved around via the internet, things can happen. Files can be corrupted, emails can be lost, or files can be accidentally deleted.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For many small marketing tasks, there is not a different between a marketing agency and a virtual assistant. But, if you are looking for more specific marketing tasks or more expertise, a marketing agency, consultant, or professional is the best way to go. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s chat in a <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery call</a> on how Marinella Yule can help further your business goals!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong>Build a Business eCourse</strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from branding to building your website to SEO to marketing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','The Difference between a Marketing Agency and a Virtual Assistant','Learn more about the difference between a marketing agency and a virtual assistant with Marinella Yule and discover which best serves your needs.','inherit','closed','closed','','1011-revision-v1','','','2020-09-23 18:47:44','2020-09-23 18:47:44','',1011,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1011-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1028,1,'2020-09-23 18:48:20','2020-09-23 18:48:20','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I recently was supposed to have a complimentary discovery call with an art gallery where we would talk about a social media strategy. Unfortunately, the woman who scheduled the call decided to ghost me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I was super excited to chat with her because I had never talked with an art gallery before, or rather, someone who runs an art gallery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I researched them and stalked their social media account to learn more about what they do, but also on how I could improve their social media and; therefore, get them more followers and sales for them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Alas, I wasn’t able to use my research to help them, but why waste good research? I decided to share my strategy notes (keeping their name private) and my steps to help you!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One thing to note: These notes are for this <em>particular </em>art gallery. Each marketing strategy needs to be molded to fit the needs and goals of the business and their target market. Feel free to book a <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery call</a> with me today to see how we can get you your perfect strategy!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Find the Target Market of the Company</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My first step to create a social media strategy is to look up the website of the company I will be assisting, in this case, the art gallery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I went through all the different pages including their Terms and Conditions and their shipping policy because, to my surprise, they ship all over the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why did this matter?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This helps me determine target market. There are some aspects of the target market I am not sure of such as age range and gender, but for the most part I could guess the age range.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How I did that was go through their product listings. Each piece of art had a price on them. The prices ranged from 1,000 to 20,000 and maybe more. Normally, 20 year old’s don’t have 20,000 lying around to spend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The price range gave me an idea that the target market is more older adults and definitely adults with more discretionary income.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Where to Implement the Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For my second step to create a social media strategy, I tried finding their social media platforms. This particular company had their Instagram and Facebook listed on their website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, as I was looking around their website, I came across their blog and on certain blog articles they had an embedded video from YouTube. After closer inspection, I found that it was their YouTube channel. I then watched a few of their videos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I saw that these videos were not posted on Instagram TV (IGTV), which I made note of.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In regards to Instagram, I realized they posted the exact same on Facebook so I busied myself with looking through their Instagram feed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I did this on my computer which showed me the number of likes per post and comments. I scrolled from posts published in 2018 till present day and saw it was a bit all over the place. Some posts had hashtags and others didn\'t and some had full on captions to barely any captions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They had a decent follow count, almost 20K, but the pictures posted within the last year was not even 10 percent. They were averaging around 30 to 40 likes per post with no comments.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I looked more in depth at the captions and realized there was no <em>call to action</em>. I will get to this later on.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The also had limited Instagram stories and they weren’t particularly engaging.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Creating the Social Media Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My next step to create a social media strategy was to then think of what was missing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Going back to the target market of high discretionary income and older adults, I thought of Pinterest. Pinterest is more of a woman platform, but it also caters to stay at home mothers and wives. Often retired women are present on the platform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I also thought of how art is a visual piece and just like Instagram, Pinterest showcases pictures and videos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A bit about me: my pet peeve is inefficiencies. When we can be efficient in our content creation the better!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the new IGTV and videos on Pinterest, there are now 3 platforms you can use to showcase your videos. You spend all this time and money on the video, use it well!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Break down the videos into little clips and post on Pinterest, break the video down into 2 (if the full video is really long) and post it on IGTV.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Remember, YouTube is more of a search engine rather than a social media platform. Which this, you can link to your YouTube video through Pinterest as well as your blog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>In Addition to the Social Media Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This step in <em>how I create a social media strategy</em> has more to do with blogging and SEO rather than social media, but it is tied together anyways.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can create blogs about videos you posted or create your own blog articles with SEO. What is SEO? Easier explanation: the keywords that you input into the article that enables it to be found on any other search engine like Google.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This will help people find your site more easily. Plus, once you create these articles you can then link to the different articles through Pinterest or YouTube (in the description box) or Instagram (link in bio).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On top of this, in regards to Instagram, I would have recommended to this art gallery to create a linktree. Please see my article on how to create a linktree on your own website why it is better than through another program.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This linktree would enable them to have multiple links through their just one link in bio on Instagram.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Creating the Content from the Social Media Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that I decided what social platforms I want to use and how to be efficient in my content creation, now I would be creating a content calendar for them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This step is more after the contract is signed, but I would have a list of ideas that I would want to discuss with them in order to formally establish a content calendar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once this step is complete, then it would be actually creating the content!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1018,\"width\":497,\"height\":497,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/20-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Creating a social media strategy by Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant\" class=\"wp-image-1018\" width=\"497\" height=\"497\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I hope this article helped you in understanding the social media strategy process and some thought processes a marketer goes through in preparation for a complimentary call or before they market your business. Feel free to schedule your <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery call</a> with me to jump start your marketing or social media strategy! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong>Build a Business eCourse</strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from target markets to building a website to SEO to marketing. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Steps in Creating a Social Media Strategy','Learn more about how Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant creates a social media strategy for clients, which can be included in a full marketing strategy.','inherit','closed','closed','','1015-revision-v1','','','2020-09-23 18:48:20','2020-09-23 18:48:20','',1015,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1015-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1029,1,'2020-09-23 18:48:47','2020-09-23 18:48:47','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Complimentary discovery calls are not as popular as one would think. Many business professionals don’t offer it and others have a strict rule on when they do jump on a call. Others still feel uncomfortable with being on a phone call let alone a video call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What? We have to put on a nice shirt? Yes, yes you do.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I offer <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery calls</a> to potential clients as a way to “meet and greet.” I use this time to get to know the potential client, but also for them to get to know me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some reasons why you should take the chance to get on a complimentary discovery call if you are the potential client and reasons if you are the business professional:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Complimentary Discovery Calls for the Potential Client</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can see the person</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Emails and messages are great, but, who is on the other side? In this age of online profiles and cat fishing, are we sure that that person’s photo is actually the person? You will be entrusting your business into the hands of this person, it is a good idea to see them “in person” or at least a video call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can ask on the spot questions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you have a video call or you meet in person, there isn’t an opportunity for the person to look up answers. As a potential client, you should want to see if the person really knows their stuff and if they don’t, how do they answer the question?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You get a feel of their personality</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Did you know, most of a message is sent via body language and tone of voice? Only like 5 percent of a message is the actual words. Talking to the person in person or via video will enable you to see how they really are. Do they have more of a vibrant personality? Do they appear more quiet and serious? There is no wrong personality, but as a potential client, you will want to work with someone who resonates with you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Reasons for the Business Professional</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can ask more in depth questions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many things to know that will help you price out a quote or to let you know if the contract fits into your niche. Sending emails and messages could cover all these questions, but often it could take many emails back and forth. Having an in person meeting or a video call will enable you to ask all the questions you need within 30 minutes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can get a sense of the scope of work</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes clients don’t know 100 percent what they are looking for. Sometimes clients say “I know it when I see it.” You might have certain phrases that are a <em>\"no go</em>\" when working with clients. Certain phrases might mean certain things about the client such as a specific project might take longer with one client than another due to the client’s personality or expectations of the work flow.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can put your best foot forward</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just as I mentioned above, most of the message is through body language and tone of voice. Before your video call or in person meeting, dress your best, brush your teeth, and make sure you are smiling! I know many women don’t like the word “Smile!” But, it really does change the conversation when you do. It conveys a happy and bright personality. Try it in the mirror. Say this with a straight face and then a smile: “My name is ___ and I love what I do.” Which sounded better?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, You can show you have studied their situation through reading your notes. People love when others do research – it shows them you care about them and their business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>For Complimentary Discovery Calls</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For myself, I use Calendly to schedule my complimentary discovery calls. It automatically sets the time for them in their time zone and then once it is scheduled, it appears in my calendar with the time in my time zone. I could also set it up to automatically send a Zoom or Google Meet link.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Make sure to follow up with them a few hours before with the link again to make sure there are no technical difficulties.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I pitch my services, I always include a sentence that discusses jumping on a call and if the person is agreeable to it, I send them the link to my Calendly. This takes away the back and forth of when both of you are available and any issues with time zone confusions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1021,\"width\":553,\"height\":553,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/23-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Complimentary Discovery Calls and why you need them with Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant\" class=\"wp-image-1021\" width=\"553\" height=\"553\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Don’t Ghost Complimentary Discovery Calls</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both the business professional and the potential client, the best and absolute must thing you have to do when it comes to complimentary discovery calls is to show up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>OR, send an email with a postponement or cancellation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It isn’t professional on either side to not show up for a scheduled call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But from another point of view, as the potential client, it is free! Why not use this time to your benefit?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The reasons for a business professional might be obvious: you will lose the potential client. But there are drawbacks for the client as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even if you decide to not hire the business professional you never know where connections will lead you. Think of complimentary discovery calls as another form of networking. Just because you can’t afford their services doesn’t mean that they might not be able to help you in other ways.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They might recommend people to you as clients for you! Or they might know of another professional that could help in your budget range.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both professional and potential client, the best rule of thumb is to be polite and positive when interacting with each other.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong>Build a Business eCourse</strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from branding to networking to invoicing to hiring someone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Complimentary Discovery Calls and Why You Need to Do Them','Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant dives in to why complimentary discovery calls are useful for both the potential client and the business professional.','inherit','closed','closed','','1013-revision-v1','','','2020-09-23 18:48:47','2020-09-23 18:48:47','',1013,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1013-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1030,1,'2020-09-23 18:52:44','2020-09-23 18:52:44','','27','','inherit','open','closed','','27','','','2020-10-01 14:46:27','2020-10-01 14:46:27','',1009,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/27.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1031,1,'2020-09-23 18:52:54','2020-09-23 18:52:54','','26','','inherit','open','closed','','26','','','2020-09-23 18:53:17','2020-09-23 18:53:17','',1009,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/26.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1032,1,'2020-09-23 18:53:46','2020-09-23 18:53:46','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have been in the business world for a few years now and have been on my own for a while as well. I have come across a few tips and tricks that can help you step up your business game.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why?</strong> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By doing these simple things, you are guaranteed to make stronger connections and potentially get more business from that.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the world of business and entrepreneurship, relationships are so important. Either they become your client or they will refer people to you. In another article, I mention how to write a rejection letter professionally in order to not burn bridges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Doing these simple things will guarantee that you will maintain bridges and potentially build even more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Keep to your meetings</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the easiest ways to step up your business game is keep your meetings. One of the biggest things I see all the time are entrepreneurs missing meetings. This might be by accident or they really didn’t put a lot of effort into it as they could have.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have been on the receiving end of missed meetings, but I also have seen many people who comment about missed meetings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One woman posted in a Facebook group that she missed two planned meetings with her client and she was hoping they would give her a third chance. I personally, would not. How can you miss two planned meetings?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I also had a potential client postpone a meeting with me four times and always at the last minute. The fifth time we were supposed to meet she didn’t email me and proceeded to stand me up. She owned her own marketing agency and I was going to help her with some of the work. I might have sent some business to her, but now, why would I?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep your meetings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Respond timely to Step Up Your Business Game</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another big complaint from entrepreneurs is that the people they hire don’t respond back to their emails in a timely manner. This can be annoying especially when a deadline is coming up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, with data and emails on our phones, it takes two seconds to send an email as acknowledgment or confirmation. This doesn’t mean you need to respond at night or during the weekends, but respond in a reasonable time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Ask Clarifying Questions</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another easy step in how to step up your business game is ask clarifying questions. Many of my clients have commented how they appreciate my clarifying questions. It shows that I am trying to make sure I understood what they are looking for and that I actually am listening or reading what they said/wrote.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This can work with entrepreneurs hiring help. Ask as many questions as you can to determine the fit between you and the actual scope of work the person can supply you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don’t be afraid to ask questions. It will only help.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Always have more details than “necessary”</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is in regards to contracts and proposals. The more details you provide the better as there will be little to no miscommunication when it comes to payment and scope of work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whenever you think you have wrote enough and have spelled out all the details enough, do more. This will step up your business game immensely. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Apologize when you made a mistake</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the best advice I can give is to apologize when you make mistakes. This shows your self-awareness and accountability. I once had a miscommunication with a client and when she wrote back to me less than happy, I responded to the effect of:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I am sorry for the confusion. There seems to be a miscommunication. Let me make the corrections to this project.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I apologized, but not in a self-deeming way, and offered to fix the situation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1030,\"width\":563,\"height\":563,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/27-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Here\'s how to step up your business game\" class=\"wp-image-1030\" width=\"563\" height=\"563\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I hope my experience and observations help you step up your business game. If you are looking for more help building up your business, feel free to send me an email and we can get started!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ways to Step Up Your Business Game','','inherit','closed','closed','','1009-revision-v1','','','2020-09-23 18:53:46','2020-09-23 18:53:46','',1009,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1009-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1033,1,'2020-09-23 18:54:44','2020-09-23 18:54:44','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have been in the business world for a few years now and have been on my own for a while as well. I have come across a few tips and tricks that can help you step up your business game.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why?</strong> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By doing these simple things, you are guaranteed to make stronger connections and potentially get more business from that.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the world of business and entrepreneurship, relationships are so important. Either they become your client or they will refer people to you. In another article, I mention how to write a rejection letter professionally in order to not burn bridges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Doing these simple things will guarantee that you will maintain bridges and potentially build even more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Keep to your meetings</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:para