closed','closed','','1107','','','2020-09-30 22:20:36','2020-09-30 22:20:36','',0,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1107/',9,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1108,0,'2020-10-01 06:46:33','2020-10-01 06:46:33','Looking for fresh buyers? Receive tons of keyword targeted visitors directly to your site. Boost your profits fast. Start seeing results in as little as 48 hours. To get details Visit: http://www.easy-web-traffic.xyz\n<!--more-->\nAUTHOR: Richelle McNicoll\nAUTHOR EMAIL: mcnicoll.richelle@gmail.com\nAUTHOR URL: \nSUBJECT: [Marinella Yule] Contact\nIP: 5.62.20.47\nArray\n(\n    [1_Name] =&gt; Richelle McNicoll\n    [2_Email] =&gt; mcnicoll.richelle@gmail.com\n    [3_Website] =&gt; \n    [4_Message] =&gt; Looking for fresh buyers? Receive tons of keyword targeted visitors directly to your site. Boost your profits fast. Start seeing results in as little as 48 hours. To get details Visit: http://www.easy-web-traffic.xyz\r\n\n    [email_marketing_consent] =&gt; \n    [entry_title] =&gt; Contact\n    [entry_permalink] =&gt; http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\n    [feedback_id] =&gt; 15301f64bca5754d4c494d3da63c680b\n)\n','Richelle McNicoll - 2020-10-01 06:46:33','','spam','closed','closed','','15301f64bca5754d4c494d3da63c680b','','','2020-10-01 06:46:33','2020-10-01 06:46:33','',145,'http://local.marinellayule.com/?post_type=feedback&p=1108',0,'feedback','',0),(1109,1,'2020-10-01 14:06:15','2020-10-01 14:06:15','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I recently was supposed to have a complimentary discovery call with an art gallery where we would talk about a social media strategy. Unfortunately, the woman who scheduled the call decided to ghost me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I was super excited to chat with her because I had never talked with an art gallery before, or rather, someone who runs an art gallery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I researched them and stalked their social media account to learn more about what they do, but also on how I could improve their social media and; therefore, get them more followers and sales for them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Alas, I wasn’t able to use my research to help them, but why waste good research? I decided to share my strategy notes (keeping their name private) and my steps to help you!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One thing to note: These notes are for this <em>particular </em>art gallery. Each marketing strategy needs to be molded to fit the needs and goals of the business and their target market. Feel free to book a <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery call</a> with me today to see how we can get you your perfect strategy!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Find the Target Market of the Company</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My first step to create a social media strategy is to look up the website of the company I will be assisting, in this case, the art gallery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I went through all the different pages including their Terms and Conditions and their shipping policy because, to my surprise, they ship all over the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why did this matter?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This helps me determine target market. There are some aspects of the target market I am not sure of such as age range and gender, but for the most part I could guess the age range.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How I did that was go through their product listings. Each piece of art had a price on them. The prices ranged from 1,000 to 20,000 and maybe more. Normally, 20 year old’s don’t have 20,000 lying around to spend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The price range gave me an idea that the target market is more older adults and definitely adults with more discretionary income.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Where to Implement the Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For my second step to create a social media strategy, I tried finding their social media platforms. This particular company had their Instagram and Facebook listed on their website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, as I was looking around their website, I came across their blog and on certain blog articles they had an embedded video from YouTube. After closer inspection, I found that it was their YouTube channel. I then watched a few of their videos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I saw that these videos were not posted on Instagram TV (IGTV), which I made note of.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In regards to Instagram, I realized they posted the exact same on Facebook so I busied myself with looking through their Instagram feed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I did this on my computer which showed me the number of likes per post and comments. I scrolled from posts published in 2018 till present day and saw it was a bit all over the place. Some posts had hashtags and others didn\'t and some had full on captions to barely any captions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They had a decent follow count, almost 20K, but the pictures posted within the last year was not even 10 percent. They were averaging around 30 to 40 likes per post with no comments.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I looked more in depth at the captions and realized there was no <em>call to action</em>. I will get to this later on.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The also had limited Instagram stories and they weren’t particularly engaging.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Creating the Social Media Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My next step to create a social media strategy was to then think of what was missing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Going back to the target market of high discretionary income and older adults, I thought of Pinterest. Pinterest is more of a woman platform, but it also caters to stay at home mothers and wives. Often retired women are present on the platform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I also thought of how art is a visual piece and just like Instagram, Pinterest showcases pictures and videos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A bit about me: my pet peeve is inefficiencies. When we can be efficient in our content creation the better!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the new IGTV and videos on Pinterest, there are now 3 platforms you can use to showcase your videos. You spend all this time and money on the video, use it well!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Break down the videos into little clips and post on Pinterest, break the video down into 2 (if the full video is really long) and post it on IGTV.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Remember, YouTube is more of a search engine rather than a social media platform. Which this, you can link to your YouTube video through Pinterest as well as your blog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>In Addition to the Social Media Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This step in <em>how I create a social media strategy</em> has more to do with blogging and SEO rather than social media, but it is tied together anyways.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can create blogs about videos you posted or create your own blog articles with SEO. What is SEO? Easier explanation: the keywords that you input into the article that enables it to be found on any other search engine like Google.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This will help people find your site more easily. Plus, once you create these articles you can then link to the different articles through Pinterest or YouTube (in the description box) or Instagram (link in bio).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On top of this, in regards to Instagram, I would have recommended to this art gallery to create a linktree. Please see my article on how to create a linktree on your own website why it is better than through another program.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This linktree would enable them to have multiple links through their just one link in bio on Instagram.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Creating the Content from the Social Media Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that I decided what social platforms I want to use and how to be efficient in my content creation, now I would be creating a content calendar for them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This step is more after the contract is signed, but I would have a list of ideas that I would want to discuss with them in order to formally establish a content calendar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once this step is complete, then it would be actually creating the content!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1018,\"width\":497,\"height\":497,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/20-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Creating a social media strategy by Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant\" class=\"wp-image-1018\" width=\"497\" height=\"497\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I hope this article helped you in understanding the social media strategy process and some thought processes a marketer goes through in preparation for a complimentary call or before they market your business. Feel free to schedule your <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery call</a> with me to jump start your marketing or social media strategy! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a></strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from target markets to building a website to SEO to marketing. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Steps in Creating a Social Media Strategy','Learn more about how Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant creates a social media strategy for clients, which can be included in a full marketing strategy.','inherit','closed','closed','','1015-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 14:06:15','2020-10-01 14:06:15','',1015,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1015-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1110,1,'2020-10-01 14:10:26','2020-10-01 14:10:26','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What is the difference between a marketing agency and a virtual assistant? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People nowadays are looking for a Virtual Assistant more and more. What is a Virtual Assistant? A Virtual Assistant is someone that is similar to a secretary or personal assistant, but online and virtually! They help in a wide range of tasks from organizing emails to customer service to some marketing tasks. The upside to Virtual Assistants is that they are usually cheaper than a marketing professional, consultant, or agency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Due to more and more business owners looking for marketing help and for a cheaper cost, entrepreneurs are turning to Virtual Assistants.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some reasons how marketing agencies and virtual assistants differ and what you need to think about before hiring one or the other.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1025,\"width\":690,\"height\":690,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/25-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"The difference between a marketing agency and a virtual assistant by Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant.\" class=\"wp-image-1025\" width=\"690\" height=\"690\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>A Marketing Agency is More Marketing Focused</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marketing Agencies are more marketing focused. Many entrepreneurs are looking for assistance in just marketing tasks. Marketing agents probably don’t offer email organizations or customer service when responding to your potential clients. However, with the marketing tasks, they know what they are doing and won’t need direct supervision or game plan. They are able to create one that best suits your business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Virtual Assistants are very smart and know their stuff. But, their stuff tends to be more email organizations, customer service, and social media media posting when they are told what and when to post. Not all of course, but many. If you have a lot of more clerical tasks, then a Virtual Assistant is the way to go. If you have more marketing tasks, consider a marketing agency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>You are Paying for the Thought Process</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One point that needs to bring up is the cost of a marketing agency versus Virtual Assistants. Virtual Assistants tend to be more budget friendly. However, marketing agencies come with a lot of marketing experience and background which justifies the higher costs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>It comes down to this question:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Would you like to hire someone who can contribute great ideas that are backed by data or someone who needs direction and is more of a support team member rather than a partner?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When looking into hiring a team member, partner, supporter, etc, look into that person’s experience and education in order to see what will be a good fit for what you are looking for.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>You Get More Ideas for Your Money</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Further into the costs, marketing agencies are always thinking of new ways to market your business efficiently and effectively. This is their bread and butter and most, if not all, marketing agencies, dream of new marketing strategies and new marketing content.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We can’t help it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even if you might be paying per hour for your marketing consultant, I guarantee you, at least for my own marketing agency, your marketing consultant is working more than what they are charging you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Further, due to a higher costs, marketing agencies probably don’t have many daily tasks for their clients. Efficient and effective marketing agencies will have their content scheduled and prepared in order to have enough time between due dates to accommodate all clients. At least, that’s how it is for my marketing agency.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Virtual Assistants tend to be hired for more daily tasks. With a more budget friendly pricing they might need to take on more clients to fill their own financial needs. This could lead them to being busy every day as they go from client to client.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>From Strategy to Content Creation to Implementation in a Marketing Agency and a Virtual Assistant</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marketing agencies are an agency. They know how the different pieces come into place. They create the strategy, create the content, and then schedule and post the content at the best times for your business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A Virtual Assistant can do this as well, but often they are required by a client or offer to their clients only content creation and or implementation. Not many Virtual Assistants can do all three.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Often, hiring multiple people can be more of a hassle than what it’s worth. It is possible to hire a marketing consultant for preparing a strategy and then giving it to someone else for content creation and then your Virtual Assistant for the implementation, but your VA might not fully understand or there might be miscommunication among the different pieces.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The more hands that are on a project, the higher the likelihood that there will be a problem. Diversity is good, but when files are being moved around via the internet, things can happen. Files can be corrupted, emails can be lost, or files can be accidentally deleted.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For many small marketing tasks, there is not a difference between a marketing agency and a virtual assistant. But, if you are looking for more specific marketing tasks or more expertise, a marketing agency, consultant, or professional is the best way to go. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s chat in a <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery call</a> on how Marinella Yule can help further your business goals!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a></strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from branding to building your website to SEO to marketing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','The Difference between a Marketing Agency and a Virtual Assistant','Learn more about the difference between a marketing agency and a virtual assistant with Marinella Yule and discover which best serves your needs.','inherit','closed','closed','','1011-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 14:10:26','2020-10-01 14:10:26','',1011,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1011-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1111,1,'2020-10-01 14:13:17','2020-10-01 14:13:17','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Complimentary discovery calls are not as popular as one would think. Many business professionals don’t offer it and others have a strict rule on when they do jump on a call. Others still feel uncomfortable with being on a phone call let alone a video call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What? We have to put on a nice shirt? Yes, yes you do.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I offer <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery calls</a> to potential clients as a way to “meet and greet.” I use this time to get to know the potential client, but also for them to get to know me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some reasons why you should take the chance to get on a complimentary discovery call if you are the potential client and reasons if you are the business professional:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Complimentary Discovery Calls for the Potential Client</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can see the person</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Emails and messages are great, but, who is on the other side? In this age of online profiles and cat fishing, are we sure that that person’s photo is actually the person? You will be entrusting your business into the hands of this person, it is a good idea to see them “in person” or at least a video call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can ask on the spot questions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you have a video call or you meet in person, there isn’t an opportunity for the person to look up answers. As a potential client, you should want to see if the person really knows their stuff and if they don’t, how do they answer the question?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You get a feel of their personality</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Did you know, most of a message is sent via body language and tone of voice? Only like 5 percent of a message is the actual words. Talking to the person in person or via video will enable you to see how they really are. Do they have more of a vibrant personality? Do they appear more quiet and serious? There is no wrong personality, but as a potential client, you will want to work with someone who resonates with you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Reasons for the Business Professional</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can ask more in depth questions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many things to know that will help you price out a quote or to let you know if the contract fits into your niche. Sending emails and messages could cover all these questions, but often it could take many emails back and forth. Having an in person meeting or a video call will enable you to ask all the questions you need within 30 minutes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can get a sense of the scope of work</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes clients don’t know 100 percent what they are looking for. Sometimes clients say “I know it when I see it.” You might have certain phrases that are a <em>\"no go</em>\" when working with clients. Certain phrases might mean certain things about the client such as a specific project might take longer with one client than another due to the client’s personality or expectations of the work flow.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You can put your best foot forward</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just as I mentioned above, most of the message is through body language and tone of voice. Before your video call or in person meeting, dress your best, brush your teeth, and make sure you are smiling! I know many women don’t like the word “Smile!” But, it really does change the conversation when you do. It conveys a happy and bright personality. Try it in the mirror. Say this with a straight face and then a smile: “My name is ___ and I love what I do.” Which sounded better?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, You can show you have studied their situation through reading your notes. People love when others do research – it shows them you care about them and their business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>For Complimentary Discovery Calls</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For myself, I use Calendly to schedule my complimentary discovery calls. It automatically sets the time for them in their time zone and then once it is scheduled, it appears in my calendar with the time in my time zone. I could also set it up to automatically send a Zoom or Google Meet link.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Make sure to follow up with them a few hours before with the link again to make sure there are no technical difficulties.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I pitch my services, I always include a sentence that discusses jumping on a call and if the person is agreeable to it, I send them the link to my Calendly. This takes away the back and forth of when both of you are available and any issues with time zone confusions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1021,\"width\":553,\"height\":553,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/23-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Complimentary Discovery Calls and why you need them with Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant\" class=\"wp-image-1021\" width=\"553\" height=\"553\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Don’t Ghost Complimentary Discovery Calls</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both the business professional and the potential client, the best and absolute must thing you have to do when it comes to complimentary discovery calls is to show up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>OR, send an email with a postponement or cancellation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It isn’t professional on either side to not show up for a scheduled call.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But from another point of view, as the potential client, it is free! Why not use this time to your benefit?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The reasons for a business professional might be obvious: you will lose the potential client. But there are drawbacks for the client as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even if you decide to not hire the business professional you never know where connections will lead you. Think of complimentary discovery calls as another form of networking. Just because you can’t afford their services doesn’t mean that they might not be able to help you in other ways.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They might recommend people to you as clients for you! Or they might know of another professional that could help in your budget range.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both professional and potential client, the best rule of thumb is to be polite and positive when interacting with each other.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a></strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from branding to networking to invoicing to hiring someone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Complimentary Discovery Calls and Why You Need to Do Them','Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant dives in to why complimentary discovery calls are useful for both the potential client and the business professional.','inherit','closed','closed','','1013-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 14:13:17','2020-10-01 14:13:17','',1013,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1013-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1112,1,'2020-10-01 14:22:27','2020-10-01 14:22:27','','35','','inherit','open','closed','','35','','','2020-10-01 14:25:22','2020-10-01 14:25:22','',1056,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/35.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1113,1,'2020-10-01 14:23:37','2020-10-01 14:23:37','','34','','inherit','open','closed','','34','','','2020-10-01 14:25:39','2020-10-01 14:25:39','',1056,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/34.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1114,1,'2020-10-01 14:27:37','2020-10-01 14:27:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What is the difference between hiring someone vs paying for an eCourse? From the outset the answer might be very obvious, but there might be some other items you haven’t thought of.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In regards to <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a>, this is a great place to get started for building your business as it will give you information that could help you hire the right person.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Hiring Someone for the Work</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>They will do it for you (you give up control)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The first thought when it comes to hiring someone is that they will do the work for you. However, the opposite viewpoint for this is that you give up control. Often, this means you have to give your passwords to your accounts to the person or you have to trust their abilities to create your vision.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>They have more training and experience (or not)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The benefit to hiring someone is that they have more training and experience in that particular area. Or, at least, you believe they do. One of the downsides of hiring someone is that in fact they don’t have the actual training and experience, which could cost you a lot more time and money than previously planned.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Hiring Someone Could Cost Hundreds of Dollars</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hiring someone, especially if they are highly trained and experienced, can cost you hundreds, if not, thousands of dollars depending on the particular job.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You have to explain what you are looking for when Hiring Someone</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The biggest downside of hiring someone vs an ecourse is that, they can’t read your mind, unfortunately. You have to explain what you are looking for. Perhaps you don’t know what you are looking for, but you know it when you see it or rather you know what you don’t want when you see it. This thought process is completely normal, but it can be costly for your time (and theirs) and your money.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Pay for an eCourse</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Saves money</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The major benefit of doing an eCourse vs hiring someone is that it saves you money. You get a lot more information for a lot less and Build a Business also gives you information on the different programs you can use and HOW you use them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>An eCourse gives information on all aspects</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build a Business eCourse goes through all the different steps of building a business online from figuring out your target market to how to price yourself to even how to network! It really does cover everything under the sun!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You have control over your baby</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let’s be honest. Our business is our baby. We have a vision for its growth. There might be a special meaning involved in your business for you. By doing an eCourse and doing the different steps yourself, you won’t have to relinquish control over your baby to someone else. You will have full control over the reigns.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>You know what you want (or don’t want)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Precisely what is mentioned above, sometimes you might not know what you want or you might only know what you DON’T want. This is totally normal. But, as mentioned above, hiring an external person is just that: an external person. They won’t be able to read your mind.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1112,\"width\":575,\"height\":575,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/35-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"hiring vs ecourse\" class=\"wp-image-1112\" width=\"575\" height=\"575\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Going through <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a> enables you to either create what is in your mind and vision yourself OR, after this course, you will have the ability to further explain your vision to that external person, which will cut down on time and, potentially, money.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Interested in learning more about Build a Business eCourse? Check out more information on this <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">page</a>. If you have follow up questions, be sure to <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">email Marinella</a> at <a href=\"mailto:myopenpassport@gmail.com\">myopenpassport@gmail.com</a>!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Hiring Someone vs an eCourse','','inherit','closed','closed','','1056-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 14:27:37','2020-10-01 14:27:37','',1056,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1056-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1115,1,'2020-10-01 14:37:57','2020-10-01 14:37:57','','36','','inherit','open','closed','','36','','','2020-10-01 14:39:04','2020-10-01 14:39:04','',1058,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/36.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1116,1,'2020-10-01 14:39:36','2020-10-01 14:39:36','','37','','inherit','open','closed','','37','','','2020-10-01 14:39:55','2020-10-01 14:39:55','',1058,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/37.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1117,1,'2020-10-01 14:44:00','2020-10-01 14:44:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build a Business eCourse is releasing soon! What is it?<a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\"> Build a Business eCourse</a> is your comprehensive e-Course that covers all the steps in building a business online from branding to SEO to setting up your website and more!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that COVID has halted in person businesses and forced many to stay at home, you might be thinking now is the time to start your own business either as a full time job or as a side gig.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Either way, don’t jump in without knowing the different parts of making a successful business!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You might be asking yourself why you need this particular eCourse. There are so many out there. Why this one?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some reasons why you need Build a Business eCourse.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Saves Hundreds of Dollars</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are hiring someone to help you set up your business online by either doing everything or just creating a website, this could cost hundreds even thousands of dollars. AND, it could even cost you much of your time coordinating with the person and discussing the different steps of the process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some other e-courses cost hundreds of dollars for one piece of information that is covered in Build a Business. Or, sometimes a course holds way more information than what you need and you end up paying for things that are not needed for you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build a Business ecourse is a budget friendly ecourse that goes through all the steps of setting up your business online from branding to SEO to setting up your website and more! You also get to pick and choose which chapters you want to purchase or you can purchase the whole course.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Get Inside Knowledge</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build a Business ecourse was created with the expertise of a marketing professional. Marinella Yule graduated from university with a marketing degree and proceeded to work in marketing in a variety of places including the US, Europe, and Canada.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Know the Info Beforehand</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If or when you do decide to hire external help, don’t go into the deal blind. Having a basic understanding of branding, SEO, marketing in general, etc will help you discuss with the person you might hire about the project. You will be able to better convey what you are looking for or ask better questions to make sure this individual is who you want to hire!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Save Time Researching Tools</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the saying goes, “time is money.” Finding the proper tools to help you start your business and or working in your business can be a hassle. We have done the research for you and give you videos on how to work the different programs so you don’t have to try them to see if they would be a good fit for you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On top of researching the different programs, we make sure to tell you the ones that also offer a free account! Perfect for budget friendly entrepreneurs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Save Time Learning the Tools</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just like the above point, we provide videos in this ecourse that gives you a brief introduction to the different programs on how to start working directly. we also provide tips and tricks to make working in the program easier and more efficient.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>One-on-one workings with Marinella</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bonus! If you decide to purchase the whole course, you will receive a one hour one-on-one meeting with Marinella on marketing, if you wish! And discounts on any additional meetings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1115,\"width\":540,\"height\":540,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/36-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Reasons why you need Build a Business eCourse\" class=\"wp-image-1115\" width=\"540\" height=\"540\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Interested in learning more about <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business e-course</a>? Check out more information on this page. If you have follow up questions, be sure to <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">email Marinella</a> at <a href=\"mailto:myopenpassport@gmail.com\">myopenpassport@gmail.com</a>!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Reasons why you need Build a Business eCourse','','inherit','closed','closed','','1058-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 14:44:00','2020-10-01 14:44:00','',1058,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1058-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1118,1,'2020-10-01 14:47:12','2020-10-01 14:47:12','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have been in the business world for a few years now and have been on my own for a while as well. I have come across a few tips and tricks that can help you step up your business game.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why?</strong> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By doing these simple things, you are guaranteed to make stronger connections and potentially get more business from that.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the world of business and entrepreneurship, relationships are so important. Either they become your client or they will refer people to you. In another article, I mention how to write a rejection letter professionally in order to not burn bridges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Doing these simple things will guarantee that you will maintain bridges and potentially build even more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Keep to your meetings</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the easiest ways to step up your business game is keep your meetings. One of the biggest things I see all the time are entrepreneurs missing meetings. This might be by accident or they really didn’t put a lot of effort into it as they could have.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have been on the receiving end of missed meetings, but I also have seen many people who comment about missed meetings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One woman posted in a Facebook group that she missed two planned meetings with her client and she was hoping they would give her a third chance. I personally, would not. How can you miss two planned meetings?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I also had a potential client postpone a meeting with me four times and always at the last minute. The fifth time we were supposed to meet she didn’t email me and proceeded to stand me up. She owned her own marketing agency and I was going to help her with some of the work. I might have sent some business to her, but now, why would I?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep your meetings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you would like to schedule a complimentary discovery call with Marinella to talk more about business or your business specifically, head over to the <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">contact page</a>!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Respond timely to Step Up Your Business Game</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another big complaint from entrepreneurs is that the people they hire don’t respond back to their emails in a timely manner. This can be annoying especially when a deadline is coming up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, with data and emails on our phones, it takes two seconds to send an email as acknowledgment or confirmation. This doesn’t mean you need to respond at night or during the weekends, but respond in a reasonable time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Ask Clarifying Questions</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another easy step in how to step up your business game is ask clarifying questions. Many of my clients have commented how they appreciate my clarifying questions. It shows that I am trying to make sure I understood what they are looking for and that I actually am listening or reading what they said/wrote.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This can work with entrepreneurs hiring help. Ask as many questions as you can to determine the fit between you and the actual scope of work the person can supply you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don’t be afraid to ask questions. It will only help.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Always have more details than “necessary”</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is in regards to contracts and proposals. The more details you provide the better as there will be little to no miscommunication when it comes to payment and scope of work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whenever you think you have wrote enough and have spelled out all the details enough, do more. This will step up your business game immensely. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Apologize when you made a mistake</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the best advice I can give is to apologize when you make mistakes. This shows your self-awareness and accountability. I once had a miscommunication with a client and when she wrote back to me less than happy, I responded to the effect of:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I am sorry for the confusion. There seems to be a miscommunication. Let me make the corrections to this project.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I apologized, but not in a self-deeming way, and offered to fix the situation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1030,\"width\":563,\"height\":563,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/27-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Here\'s how to step up your business game\" class=\"wp-image-1030\" width=\"563\" height=\"563\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I hope my experience and observations help you step up your business game. If you are looking for more help building up your business, feel free to <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">send me an email</a> and we can get started!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a></strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from discovering your target marketing to networking to SEO to invoicing and making contracts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ways to Step Up Your Business Game','Learn more about these easy ways you can step up your business game with Marinella Yule Marketer in order to continue to reach your business goals. ','inherit','closed','closed','','1009-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 14:47:12','2020-10-01 14:47:12','',1009,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1009-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1119,1,'2020-10-01 14:49:57','2020-10-01 14:49:57','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is a debate on how necessary it is for a marketer to have a strong social media presence. There are two sides in this debate and both have valid points. At the end of the day, it depends on you, the potential client, what you prefer in your marketer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1041,\"width\":544,\"height\":544,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/33-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Does your marketer\'s social media presence matter? \" class=\"wp-image-1041\" width=\"544\" height=\"544\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Social Media Presence is Important</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a potential client or an entrepreneur looking for some help in growing your business, seeing a marketer online that has a lot of followers and comments looks appealing.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You look at it and might think to yourself: “<em>They look like they know what they are doing.</em>”&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hopefully, they are giving you advice that they use so you can reach a high follower count and meet your sales goals.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why mess with a winning formula?&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Social Media Presence is NOT Important</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you are looking for some social media help, you might come across some marketers. You want to learn more about them and see if they know what they are talking about.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You check out their social media accounts and they don’t have such a high following or comment rate. This might make you pause and think: “<em>Do they know what they are talking about?</em>”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a good question and not an abnormal one.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Here is one thought to consider: </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Perhaps they don’t have a strong presence because they are busy working with their clients? Perhaps that other marketer has a huge following because they don’t spend a lot of time with their own clients?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>The Answer to the Debate?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is no wrong answer in this debate. Not all marketers who have a strong following don’t have extra time for their clients just as how some marketers really don’t know what they are talking about with a low social media presence.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With everything, it depends on the case and the marketer.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In terms of social media, it depends on the industry. Remember, some industries are pretty saturated such as travel. It is hard to spread your message or become an influencer in this industry.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But, if you have more a niche, it might be easier to expand and grow.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Social Media Presence Takes Time</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Either way, social media takes time. This might be why you are looking for some help. It takes time to think of what to post, write the caption, and actually post or schedule.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, you have to engage with followers and others.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It takes time.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can apply this thought process when looking for your own marketer. Are they spending time on their own accounts or are they spending most of their time with clients?&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is hard to know just from looking at their accounts, but many marketers have a portfolio that you can view or a case study of accounts they have grown in the past.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Types of Marketers’ Social Media Accounts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, social media presence is important. Not only for business awareness, but also to share who you are with potential clients, if you are the marketer.&nbsp;Also, marketers look at potential clients\' social media to see more about their business, but also the personality of the potential client.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marketers tend to have two different types of profiles:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>The Marketing Profile</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This profile allows the marketer to share their ideas and give marketing advice to their followers. It allows them to share their knowledge and “<em>strut their stuff.</em>” This enables trust in the marketer’s skills and experience.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Who am I profile</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This profile, more <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://www.instagram.com/myopenpassport/\" target=\"_blank\">my style,</a> is showing clients who I am and what I love to do. Though it is a business relationship, it is also more than exchange of goods and cash. I am working with an entrepreneur and their business closely, we need to know each other and feel comfortable with each other. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The biggest point: <em>we need to trust each other</em>. Even if the marketer lacks in certain skills, does the entrepreneur trust them enough to believe they can still do the job? The answer might come from seeing their hobbies and life from their profile.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a potential client as well as a marketer, it is up to you what aspect you want to portray or want to see in social media. Again, there is no wrong or right answer in this debate. It depends entirely on each and every person.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are looking for help with your marketing needs, feel free to reach out and set up a <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">complimentary discovery call</a> today!&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a></strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from target markets to building a website to marketing to networking.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Does Your Marketer’s Social Media Presence Matter?','Jump into this debate to discover if your marketer\'s social media presence matters when it comes to marketing knowledge with Marinella Yule Marketer.','inherit','closed','closed','','1003-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 14:49:57','2020-10-01 14:49:57','',1003,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1003-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1120,1,'2020-10-01 14:56:43','2020-10-01 14:56:43','','38','','inherit','open','closed','','38','','','2020-10-01 14:57:03','2020-10-01 14:57:03','',1062,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/38.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1121,1,'2020-10-01 14:57:20','2020-10-01 14:57:20','','39','','inherit','open','closed','','39','','','2020-10-01 14:58:03','2020-10-01 14:58:03','',1062,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/39.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1122,1,'2020-10-01 15:02:01','2020-10-01 15:02:01','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a> is a comprehensive course for new online entrepreneurs. This course could also apply for experienced entrepreneurs who are looking to bring their business online. It goes through all the steps needed to make sure your business is as successful as it can be online from branding to SEO to networking.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even if you already have branding done, it is good to make sure it is what you want or if you do want to change it, this chapter would give you the tools to do so by yourself.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This being said, here are some reasons that Build a Business eCourse is for you!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Are you looking for step by step guide on starting an online business by yourself?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As mentioned, this course has a chapter on different steps that you will need to address when establishing your online presence for your business.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can choose to do the whole course or pieces of the course. But either way, this course gives you a step by step guide from start to…..having a good basis to launch your business!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Do you have extra time or looking to get extra income?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With COVID, you might have found yourself with some extra time at home or you might be looking for some extra income. Something that you can do at home, online, away from people, because COVID.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This course gives you the knowledge to do just that!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Do you like being in charge and control over projects?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This course is for those entrepreneurs who are looking to do-it-themselves. If you are looking to hire someone for certain aspects of your business, this course will also give you insight into what to look for when hiring and how to communicate with that person on how to bring your business vision to life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Do you like learning new things?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you like learning new things especially when it comes to business and entrepreneurship, this course is also for you! We cover a variety of topics including some of the confusing website platforms and hosting, SEO, and invoicing programs.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This course doesn’t just cover social media!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>An Experienced and Trained Host</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are looking for a course that is ran by someone who has the experience and training then <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a> is for you! This course was created by Marinella Yule who studied marketing in university and then proceeded to work in a variety of places including USA, Europe, and Canada.  She incorporates her own experience and her observations of other entrepreneurs in order to make sure your business is built firmly! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>YES! FOR YOU!</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1121,\"width\":658,\"height\":658,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/39-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Is Build a Business eCourse for You?\" class=\"wp-image-1121\" width=\"658\" height=\"658\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If all of the above resonated with you then yes! This course is for you! <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Click here</a> to learn more or if you have any follow up questions about Build a Business and or your host, Marinella, feel free to send an email to <a href=\"mailto:myopenpassport@gmail.com\">myopenpassport@gmail.com</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Is Build a Business eCourse for You?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1062-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 15:02:01','2020-10-01 15:02:01','',1062,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1062-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1123,1,'2020-10-01 15:38:06','2020-10-01 15:38:06','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many have forgone the art of negotiation, but in this article, I will dive into when and where we can implement it to build up your business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a marketing professional, I have to send proposals for work all the time to potential clients. Often potential clients want an estimate or ballpark range rather than an official proposal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What is the difference between an estimate or ballpark range with an official proposal?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Estimate and Ballpark Range</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An estimate/ballpark range is a guess on what the price could be. Often, at least for me, I tend to give a higher estimate than what the official proposal will actually be.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marketers only know about the scope of work from what you tell them. Usually, the scope of work outlined is just that, an outline. Marketers need to ask more questions, analyze what has already been done, go over what improvements could be done. This takes more than a few minutes to process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When a marketer gives an estimate or ballpark range there is so much they haven’t factored. They assume the work will take a lot more than it might because they haven’t analyzed everything yet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Official Proposal</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The official proposal takes into account all of the questions, all of the analysis, everything. It is sent via a professionally made PDF that lists out everything included in the quote.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For me, I usually give an official proposal after talking with the potential client either in person, over the phone, or via video call. Though, I prefer in person or video call the best.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>What to Look for in a Proposal</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you aren’t sure what you should be expecting in an official proposal, here is a list of items I make sure to include when I send out my official proposal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Date of proposal – sometimes proposals have an expiration date</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>What the goal of the project is</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>The two parties involved (the marketer and the potential client)</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>The different tasks</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For example, if it is social media, does it include content creation, scheduling, engagement? How often the posts are scheduled, Which platforms, etc</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Who is supplying the content calendar and strategy for the social media example</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Quote</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The quote can be a full packaged quote</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes I also give a breakdown quote, what specific items will cost, for example, each content calendar is $X and a month of graphics to post is $Y.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>How and When the invoice will be dealt with</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For both marketers and clients, having everything listed out makes sure both parties are on the same page with what to expect from the price being paid. At the end of the day, both parties need to be happy when the invoice comes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1035,\"width\":576,\"height\":576,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/29-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"The art of negotiation, getting the most for your money\" class=\"wp-image-1035\" width=\"576\" height=\"576\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Negotiation Can Be An Option</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, after an estimate is given or even after an official proposal, a potential client could negotiate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This depends on the marketer. Some marketers have set prices for set packages on their website. If they quoted you what is exactly on their website, they might not be up for negotiating. If the marketer, such as myself, gives a <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/rates/\">custom quote</a>, they might be open to negotiating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marketers have had experience on the <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/services/\">types of services</a> they provide meaning they know what they can move around to fit a specific budget. They also know what specific tasks are reasonable for your budget.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don’t be afraid to ask further questions on the quote especially with an estimate or ballpark range.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is especially true with you have connected with the marketer during your meeting or video call. Please see my article on why complimentary discovery calls or meeting is the best option.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Negotiation Steps</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not sure how negotiation works? Here are some quick steps!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Receive the estimate</li><li>Analyze the price difference between the estimate and your own budget range</li><li>Prioritize the list of tasks you want to outsource, which do you need help for sure right now</li><li>Send back an email or jump on a call with the marketer and list out your concerns with the budget and ask for some wiggle room with the quote.</li><li>The marketer should respond with what they could offer</li><li>Lay out what you absolutely need</li><li>At this point, the marketer should respond with a lower quote or offer to help you find a suitable person</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I hope this article has helped you in the process for finding a marketer or handling quotes with clients. Feel free to book a complimentary call with me and we can discuss more about marketing your own service business or to see how I can help you bring your brand voice to life!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be sure to keep an eye out for the <strong><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a></strong>! This will help you conquer your business goals! The course will dive into the different aspects of building your business online from branding to contracts to invoicing to hiring someone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','The Art of Negotiation','Learn more about negotiating and how it can be beneficial to you and your business with Marinella Yule Marketing Consultant. ','inherit','closed','closed','','1007-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 15:38:06','2020-10-01 15:38:06','',1007,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1007-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1124,1,'2020-10-01 15:43:46','2020-10-01 15:43:46','','40','','inherit','open','closed','','40','','','2020-10-01 15:45:45','2020-10-01 15:45:45','',1060,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/40.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1125,1,'2020-10-01 15:45:57','2020-10-01 15:45:57','','41','','inherit','open','closed','','41','','','2020-10-01 15:46:19','2020-10-01 15:46:19','',1060,'http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/41.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1126,1,'2020-10-01 15:46:49','2020-10-01 15:46:49','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>First, what is an eCourse? An eCourse is a course online. Courses can cover a variety of information from history to math to marketing. They can also be a variety of prices. Some can be hundreds of dollars and others can be free.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">Build a Business eCourse</a> covers all the items you need to get started creating your business online. From my own online business journey and talking with my own clients who are starting out, I realized there was a need for budget friendly or do-it-yourself course out there for new online entrepreneurs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many of the eCourses out there are very specialized in certain information such as one course just on social media marketing. One course just on social media content creation. One course on coding.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It can be tiring for entrepreneurs to keep buying different courses from different sources. Wouldn’t it be better to buy from one shop?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some ways that Build a Business eCourse is different and will help you succeed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Talks about Pricing</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A lot of business eCourses really focus on marketing and design. Many don’t talk about how to price yourself, how to invoice, and all the other information on numbers. Build a Business jumps into these details and goes over different ways in order for you to pick the best way for you!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Talks about Networking</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Surprisingly, networking has been one of my top questions from clients and other business professionals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/in-person-and-online-networking/\">“How do you network?”</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This question comes up a lot either in how to start a conversation or how to network during COVID or online times.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build a Business offers a chapter focused on these questions! A big part of starting a business is networking and building a professional network. You can start this at any time, even before you have your website up!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Talks about some Coding</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build a Business is not a coding eCourse. If you are looking for a straight up coding course, this isn’t it. However, Build a Business does cover basic coding information and vocabulary. When building or maintaining your website you might find yourself needing some basic coding. This chapter covers basic coding vocabulary and how to read the code.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Talks about SEO</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a new online entrepreneur, it is never to early to start learning and implementing SEO. Even starting your website, you need to think about SEO because going back and updating it can be a hassle.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This chapter dives into SEO vocabulary and where you can start implementing and free tools you can use to make your online presence stand out.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Buy ALL or Buy separately, have for a lifetime</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build a Business offers multiple chapters under one course. This means that you can buy each chapter separately. If you just want the SEO and Networking chapter, you can buy just those. If you don’t want the Branding chapter, you are not required to pay for it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the reverse, if you do want to buy all the chapters, you get a discount on the full package!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Plus, you get to keep the information for a lifetime!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Each chapter has written and video material for learners of all types</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build a Business provides materials for all types of learners. Are you more of a reader? We have worksheets. Are you more of a listener or like watching how it is done? We have videos!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1124,\"width\":517,\"height\":517,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/40-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"How Build a Business eCourse is different\" class=\"wp-image-1124\" width=\"517\" height=\"517\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Interested in learning more about Build a Business eCourse? Check out more information on this <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/build-a-business-ecourse-2/\">page</a>. If you have follow up questions, be sure to <a href=\"http://local.marinellayule.com/contact/\">email Marinella</a> at <a href=\"mailto:myopenpassport@gmail.com\">myopenpassport@gmail.com</a>!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How Build a Business eCourse is Different','Learn how Build a Business eCourse is different from the other business eCourse and how you can start building today with Marinella Yule.','inherit','closed','closed','','1060-revision-v1','','','2020-10-01 15:46:49','2020-10-01 15:46:49','',1060,'http://local.marinellayule.com/1060-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1127,1,'2020-10-01 15:49:48','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This website has been has been built by Marinella Yule.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'re keen to give everyone a voice, regardless of their ability or technical know how. We have incorporated expert advice to make sure that the software our website is built on, meets or, wherever possible exceeds <a href=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WCAG 2.1, the current global web accessibility standard</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We were also given guidance from programmers to ensure this site\'s content also meets these standards.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Let us know if you have difficulties using this site</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whilst we have spent a lot of time ma